insert into articles_description (articles_id, language_id, articles_name, articles_description, articles_head_desc_tag, articles_url, articles_viewed) values ('4', '1', 'Privacy Policy', '<p>El Mall de la Esquina has adopted this policy in connection with the collection, use and disclosure of information that you may provide through this website. By using this website, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy. If you have questions that are not answered below, you may contact us at: client@elmalldelaesquina.com. You can also reach us at: 1-814-753-0801<br />El Mall de la Esquina LLC<br />Attention: Privacy Office<br />2267 Setter Run Ln - Suite 112<br />State College, PA 16801<br />Why do we Collect and Use Your Information?<br />We collect Personal Information when you: <br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Transact with us by utilizing the services available on the website<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Create an Account and become a Member of the website<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Contact us, provide comments or feedback, participate in social media (such as Facebook or Twitter) through the website, or sign up to receive newsletters, alerts, or special offers from us<br />We use your Personal Information to: <br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide services to you and complete transactions (e.g., receiving and processing payment for your purchase of products available on the website)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide customer support<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Contact you if problems should arise during any business transaction<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide special offers from us or our affiliates or marketing partners which may be of interest to you<br />All of this Personal Information is provided directly by you at your discretion.<br />We may automatically collect certain Non-Personal Information about you, such as: <br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The type of browser or computer operating system you use and the domain name that referred you to our website<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;An Internet Protocol Address (an \"IP Address\")<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Your navigation behaviour (for example, the designers you purchase, pages you view, and the links you click).<br />This Non-Personal Information can be passively collected (that is, gathered without you actively providing the information) using Cookies and other web technologies. These help make your visit to our website easier, more efficient and more valuable by providing you with a customized experience and recognizing you when you return.<br />We use the Non-Personal Information to: <br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Help us analyse the effectiveness and enhance the usefulness of our marketing efforts<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide better service to website visitors<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Customize this website based on user preferences<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Compile and analyse statistics and trends<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Administer and improve this website for your use<br />Non-Personal information may also be collected during your use of the website by third party advertisers, service providers and marketing partners with whom we have relationships and who use their own cookies, internet tags, or web beacons to collect information. If they do, such information may then be used to provide advertising directed to you and tailored to your interests.<br />How can you opt out of the use of Cookies and the Receipt of e-mail?<br />Depending on the Web browser you use, you may be able to block or disable cookies by following the instructions in the toolbar on your Web browser. If you block cookies, you will still be able to use the El Mall de la Esquina website; however, your browser will not remember your personal preferences when you return to this website, and some features of this website may not be available. Additionally, you may opt out of advertisement emails and alerts from us and third party advertisers by simply clicking on the \"unsubscribe\" link on the emails and alerts.<br />How will Your Information be Shared?<br />We respect your privacy, and we do not sell, transfer, or otherwise share your Personal Information to third parties except our affiliates and our service providers for business-related purposes. In addition, we may share your Personal Information with carefully selected marketing partners with whom we work who may then offer you additional products or services that we think may be of interest to you. We hope you are delighted with what we send your way, but you may choose at any time to tell El Mall de la Esquina to discontinue sharing your Personal Information with our marketing partners. You can let us know by logging into your account and updating your email preferences under the \"My Account\" tab.<br />We may also share information to (1) comply with applicable law or regulation; (2) enforce the terms of any of our agreements; (3) protect the security or integrity of this website or the rights, property or safety of El Mall de la Esquina or others; (4) respond to regulatory or governmental information requests; (5) exercise our legal rights; or (6) respond to legal processes.<br />By providing any Personal Information to us you fully understand and consent to the transfer, processing and storage of such information as described herein.<br />We reserve the right to transfer your Personal Information to a third party in the event of a sale, merger, liquidation, acquisition or similar event.<br />Can Minors use the Website?<br />This website and its offerings are not intended for individuals under 18 years old. We do not knowingly solicit data online from, or market online to, children under 13. If we knowingly receive a child&rsquo;s Personal Information, we will delete it from our systems.<br />How Secure is Your Information?<br />We value your privacy, and for that reason we take steps to store and maintain personally identifiable information that you transmit through our website or otherwise provide to us. We protect such information from loss, misuse, and unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration or destruction through the use of encryption and other industry standard protective measures. However, no method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage is ever completely secure or error-free. Therefore, while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its security.<br />What About Links to Other Websites?<br />This website and Privacy Policy may contain links or references to other websites as a convenience to visitors to this website. This Privacy Policy will not apply to those websites. Those website privacy policies (if any) will apply.<br />Could There be Changes to this Privacy Policy?<br />We reserve the right to change our Privacy Policy from time to time. If we change our Privacy Policy, we will post the modified Privacy Policy on this website. Unless stated otherwise, our current Privacy Policy applies to all information that we have about you.<br />Where will Your Information be Processed?<br />By providing any Personal Information to the website, all users fully understand and consent to this Privacy Policy and to the transfer of such Personal Information across international borders in compliance with all applicable laws as part of our operation, including the collection, storage, and processing of such information within the United States of America.<br />El Mall de la Esquina is a Pennsylvania corporation that owns and controls this website and all information, content, and services available on this website as a service for its Account Members.<br /><br /><br /></p>', '', '', '0');
